<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-03-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-03-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="154" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d154">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <hi rend="italic"><date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-03-28">March 28,
                                    1906</date></hi>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Wilson reports that, under the department’s telegraphic instructions
                            received February 23 and March 25, he has been strongly urging the
                            Government of Japan to give real effect to their avowed open-door policy
                            in Manchuria and says that he hopes to report soon a definite answer to
                            his notes. Representations are also being made by the British
                            Government.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>